                                                <b>AdHocQuery</b> - Search parameters are saved, but not run automatically; you can manually run the query against the entire MEDLINE database at any time.<br>
                                            </td>

                                            <td align="right" valign="top" width="10%">
                                                <img src="~/Content/images/icon_savedsearch_active.gif" border="0" height="32" width="32"></td>
                                            <td valign="top" width="40%">
                                                <b>AutoQuery</b> - Search parameters are saved, and optionally run automatically against new MEDLINE data every week. You can also request that ACR Journal Advisor send you a weekly email updating you on the status of your active AutoQueries.<br>
                                            </td>

